Base URL
http://localhost:8080/api/products

1. Create Product
POST /api/products
Request Body
{
  "name": "Red T-Shirt",
  "description": "Comfort cotton t-shirt",
  "price": 199.99,
  "stock": 50,
  "sku": "TSHIRT_RED_001"
}

Response 201 Created
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Red T-Shirt",
  "description": "Comfort cotton t-shirt",
  "price": 199.99,
  "stock": 50,
  "sku": "TSHIRT_RED_001",
  "createdAt": "2025-12-09T10:34:48.329073Z",
  "updatedAt": "2025-12-09T10:34:48.329073Z"
}

2. Get Product by ID
GET /api/products/{id}
Example Response
{
  "id": 7,
  "name": "Product 4",
  "description": "Description for product 4",
  "price": 493.67,
  "stock": 70,
  "sku": "SKU0004",
  "createdAt": "2025-12-01T10:09:10.50661Z",
  "updatedAt": "2025-12-09T10:44:54.754926Z"
}

3. Get All Products (Paginated + Sorted)
GET /api/products?page=0&size=10&sort=name,asc
Response Structure

Top-level fields come directly from Spring Data Page object.

